Former Oudtshoorn municipal manager Martin Pietersen was found guilty earlier this month of swindling the municipality out of more than R2 million. CAPE TOWN - A former Oudtshoorn municipal manager convicted of corruption will hear his fate in the George Magistrates Court at the end of March next year.It was alleged that from October 2010 to June 2011 that 60-year-old Martin Noel Pietersen misused his authority by authorising wasteful expenditure in favour of a private company he was allegedly linked to.Pietersen was found guilty earlier this month of swindling the municipality out of more than R2 million.He was arrested in August 2013.Hawks spokesperson Lloyd Ramovha said: &quot;The ruling is understood to be the first of its kind in the country and it emanates from five charges in contravention of Section 173 of the Municipal Finance Management Act.&quot;(Edited by Zunaid Ismael)